* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˌʃaŋˈhaɪ/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈʃeɪŋ.haɪ/|/ˌʃeɪŋˈhaɪ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-shanghai.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪ}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To force or trick (someone) into joining a ship which is lacking a full crew.
#* '''1999''' June 24, ‘The Resurrection of Tom Waits’, in ''Rolling Stone'', quoted in ''Innocent When You Dream'', Orion (2006), page 256,
#*: It was the strangest galley: the sounds, the steam, he's screaming at his coworkers.  I felt like I'd been '''shanghaied'''.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To abduct or coerce.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[commandeer]]; [[appropriate]]; [[hijack]]
#: ''Let's see if we can '''shanghai''' a room for a couple of hours.''

